article.headline: Richmond 89, UNC-Greensboro 63
article.story: RICHMOND, Va. -- David Gonzalves had a season-high 25 points to lead Richmond to an 89-63 win over North Carolina-Greensboro on Tuesday. Gonzalves scored 16 points in the first half as the Spiders (9-3) finished the half on an 11-4 run to claim a 40-31 lead at halftime, despite the Spartans (2-8) scoring the first eight points of the game. Richmond put the game away by hitting four 3-pointers -- two by Anderson -- in a three-minute span early in the second half to take a 62-48 lead with 11:58 left. Anderson scored 12 of his 16 points in the second half, Dan Geriot had 13 off the bench and Justin Harper added 10. Richmond had a season highs with 10 blocks and 15 steals on 20 turnovers by the Spartans. Richmond hit 55.4 percent from the floor -- 11-for-22 from beyond the arc. Brandon Evans led N.C.-Greensboro with a season-high 22 points.
